{"id":14880806,"mediaExerciseId":"e670be7c-3b5b-407c-9d25-4c08e5083899","exerciseName":"11","chapterName":"3","chapterTitle":"Working with Financial Statements","groupId":612275,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":86,"solutions":[{"id":5962953,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we are required to determine the EBITDA multiple for the company.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/af639eaf564ff5bf6141ae3bbad987d7/4a1638663b2ac7415eecc6aa9cf652ea/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/af639eaf564ff5bf6141ae3bbad987d7/4a1638663b2ac7415eecc6aa9cf652ea/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we begin, let us first define EBITDA.\n\n**Earnings Before Interest, Taxes, Depreciation, and Amortization or EBITDA** measures a company's overall financial performance which shows earnings before the effect of accounting and financial deductions.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/af639eaf564ff5bf6141ae3bbad987d7/0813de89b706dac2404c4217adf3e2fa/lateximg_large.png","width":1060},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/af639eaf564ff5bf6141ae3bbad987d7/0813de89b706dac2404c4217adf3e2fa/lateximg.png","width":529}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"**EBITDA Multiple** is a financial ratio that measures the company's return on investment.\n\nThe formula is denoted as follows:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{EBITDA Multiple}& =\n \\dfrac{\\text{Enterprise Value}} {\\text{EBITDA}}\\\\ \\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":203,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/af639eaf564ff5bf6141ae3bbad987d7/1fef6314055478b1177a230654b1d5fe/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":102,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/af639eaf564ff5bf6141ae3bbad987d7/1fef6314055478b1177a230654b1d5fe/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we can determine the EBITDA multiple, first let us determine the EBITDA:\n\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{EBITDA}& =\n\\text{EBIT + Depreciation \\& Amortization}\\\\ \\\\\n&=\\$91,000 + \\$157,000 \\\\ \\\\\n&=\\boxed{\\$248,000}\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\\\nAs can be see, the EBITDA is $248,000.\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Next, we need to determine the enterprise value:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{Enterprise value}& =\n\\text{Market value of the equity + Debt - Cash}\\\\ \\\\\n&=\\$645,000 + \\$215,000 - \\$53,000 \\\\ \\\\\n&=\\boxed{\\$807,000}\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\\\nAs can be see, the Enterprise value is $807,000.\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Now that we have determined the EBITDA and the enterprise value, we can already determine the EBITDA multiple.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{EBITDA Multiple}& =\n \\dfrac{\\text{Enterprise Value}} {\\text{EBITDA}}\\\\ \\\\\n& = \\frac{\\$807,000} {\\$248,000}\\\\ \\\\\n&= \\boxed{3.25}\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\\\nIn conclusion, the EBITDA multiple is **3.25** times.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":442,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/af639eaf564ff5bf6141ae3bbad987d7/649e3b42a07ace60f531762f578dc2e1/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":222,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/af639eaf564ff5bf6141ae3bbad987d7/649e3b42a07ace60f531762f578dc2e1/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"3.25","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":22,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/af639eaf564ff5bf6141ae3bbad987d7/db12f86fdb485f51080c96be3983e7b5/lateximg_large.png","width":51},"regular":{"height":11,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/af639eaf564ff5bf6141ae3bbad987d7/db12f86fdb485f51080c96be3983e7b5/lateximg.png","width":27}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":true,"stepNumber":7}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"1f441882-332b-4b8b-842e-a529ad1f4347","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":7}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880807,"exerciseName":"12","page":86,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"9bb4c78d-6a22-4158-bbfc-d5e6289af2bb","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-3-questions-and-problems-12-9bb4c78d-6a22-4158-bbfc-d5e6289af2bb"},{"id":14880808,"exerciseName":"13","page":86,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"0d0b8c75-a4b2-4be5-b7a5-5caade70b390","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-sol